			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Fix the collision graphics.  At the very least, do not permit mobs to walk through walls and closed doors. A newbie sitting in an EC building should not have to worry about a cat jumping him by walking through a wall.  Do not have mobs walking up trees instead of around them. Do not EVER let a mob that cannot be touched by a player be capable of engaging in melee with a player (seen a good bit of this in ME around the UP zone line lately. Drop the "anti exploit" code that has mobs warping impossibly to attack players when they feel they have waited too long to reach them (hint: fixing the bad pathing would help almost as much). Do not spawn mobs by having them fall from the sky; let them fade in the way looted corpses now fade out.  On a more mage-specific level, do not let our pets poof into the world when we move near the wall; if mobs can warp when they're stuck for 5 seconds, our pets can warp back to us (although it would be better if the issue never came up). 
<br />

<br />
It's a graphics-intensive environment. All of the lovely effects and atmospherics are ruined when this kind of visually jarring crap occurs. It also messes up gameplay (had a group member die in NC yesterday when a mob decided to warp to him because the pathing made it think it was being exploited, even though he was just about ten feet in front of it).  
<br />

<br />
None of this is anywhere close to being as important as the stuff you say you don't want to hear about here, but it is basic to the game and should be fixed for everybody's sake.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
