				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Lot of the points are already hit (though I would ask for a class definition before ANYTHING else is done), but here's ideas anyways:
<br />
<ul><li><span style="text-decoration: underline">Look at the cost of LDoN items that are meant for certain levels</span>: I would bet that if you did straight LDoNs from level 20 (or whenever you start them) that it would be IMPOSSIBLE to get your level 39 spells on time.  And then lvl 44 spells.  And then whatever.  Only when you hit your 60s can you actually go back any buy some of those spells, since they actually give a decent amount of points.  So either adjust the cost on the low-end stuff WAY down, or increase the points given DRAMATICALLY.  Like 100pts lvl 65 normal, 200 hard, and give 75 for the lvl 58 dungeons, 50 for 53, 40 for 48, 35 for 43, 25 for 38, etc.  People do NOT spend all their time in LDoN (nor do most want to), so I would say increase points given a LOT to make it seem like you are actually making progress, especially at the low-end.
<br />
<li><span style="text-decoration: underline">Help the people in the 30s</span>: This may be a personal pet peeve, but I REALLY hate leveling alts through the 30s.  Nowhere seems to give good exp.  FAR too few people lfg in that range to do LDoNs without spending 1.5-2hrs even putting the group together, and the zones traditionally meant for that range (overthere, dawnshroud) just do NOT give good exp.  And people are always reluctant to go into dungeons, even if they ARE hotspots (even though we all know hotspots are BS).  So just generally do SOMETHING to this level range.  It is NEVER fun to level through it.  And the tasks so far aren't cutting it.  Telling somebody to kill 10 things in a DANGEROUS zone where you can't even FIND the mobs isn't fun, even for a soloing class (asked my 37 necro to kill 10 plaguebone skels in EJ.  Killing them is easy.  Finding them is f'n hard, even with sense undead because of all the OTHER undead around.  And then you get chased to CoM by the tigers and monkeys which are red.  NOT fun).
<br />
<li><span style="text-decoration: underline">Shadowhunter</span>: put this guy on a 3-day re-spawn or something.  VERY annoying.  Even Gorenaire wasn't this big of a problem because she (he?) didn't wander into the exp parts of Dreadlands all that often (before killed regularly these days of course).  Gorenaire killed me a total of once in 10 levels and probably 100+ hours (on all my chars) spent in dreadlands (probably more).  I've been killed at LEAST 6 times (probably 7 or 8) in the last WEEK from Shadowhunter.  If you're not willing to change the re-spawn, then just put the agro range down so that you can actually SEE him before he agroes.  Agro monsters fine.  Agro monsters that one-round you i'm not too hot about, but I can deal with.  Agro monsters that one round you, agro before you see them, and have near-bard speed is NOT fun.  Especially not in an exp zone.</ul>
<br />
I'll probably think of others later, but that's a good start.<br />_________________<br />Eriol Telcontar
<br />
Arch Convoker - Master of the Orb
<br />
The Tribunal
<br />

<br />
Eriol
<br />
20 Necromancer - 22 Jeweler - Blackburrow</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
