			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is something I'd generally put on EQRoleplayers under my "cleric" hat rather than on The Magician's Tower under my "mage" hat, but I see no thread on this anywhere else, and this little issue has been my number one gripe for the last five years, so here it is.
<br />

<br />
======================================
<br />

<br />
A tiny simple fix every roleplayer has asked for since EQ was released, and EQRoleplayers has been begging for since its creation. Expand the "/anon" command and it's affect on /who and /lfg listings, and thereby allow the change to the "/roleplay" command to make it actually usable by roleplayers for designating roleplayed characters AND HAVE NO OTHER EFFECT that makes it desirable for non-roleplayers to use. This way, the "RP" tag will have have a chance to MEAN that one might reasonably expect characters who wear it to actually be roleplayed.
<br />

<br />
One solution is to make the "/anon" command take some options. For example, make "/anon all" do what "/anon" does now. Make "/anon guild" do exactly what "/roleplay" does now, but without the colour change to the nametag. Make "/anon none" bring everything back to open view (nothing hidden). Perhaps give some other "/anon XXX" options for other combinations, but that is not vital at all. For example:
<br />

<br />
/anon none
<br />
/who all Suzanna
<br />
[67 Arch Convoker] Suzanna &lt; Heroes of the Old Lands &gt; [zone info]
<br />
/anon guild
<br />
/who all Suzanna
<br />
[ANONYMOUS] Suzanna &lt; Heroes of the Old Lands &gt;
<br />
/anon all
<br />
/who all Suzanna
<br />
[ANONYMOUS] Suzanna 
<br />

<br />
Whilst doing this, adding RACE into the list for /who and /lfg would be even better, as it allows roleplayers to choose alignment-compatible people at a glance, not always needing them to enquire (/tell XXX ooc: what race is your character please?). Not that Suzanna the agnostic mage cares a hoot what race another character is, but that is NOT true for a certain roleplayed zealous cleric I play ...
<br />

<br />
The reason for all this though is, to allow you to change "/roleplay" to have only one purpose - to designate that character as roleplayed. This would then mean there is no reason for any player to use the "/roleplay" tag UNLESS they actually mean it to indicate that the character is infact roleplayed. In other words, make the "/roleplay" tag MEAN exactly what it says! This new "/roleplay" indication would need to be able to stack with any setting of "/anon", as there should not be any reason for people to not be able to use it AND use the "/anon" setting of their choice, or once again it would create a reason NOT to use it for some players who might otherwise. The effect of the "/roleplay" command will be simply and only to toggle the nametag colour change and add a "[RP]" to the end of the nametag and to "/who" and "/lfg" listings. For example:
<br />

<br />
/anon none
<br />
/roleplay
<br />
[67 Arch Convoker] Suzanna &lt; Heroes of the Old Lands &gt; [zone info] [RP]
<br />
/anon guild
<br />
/roleplay
<br />
/who all Suzanna
<br />
[ANONYMOUS] Suzanna &lt; Heroes of the Old Lands &gt; [RP]
<br />
/anon all
<br />
/roleplay
<br />
/who all Suzanna
<br />
[ANONYMOUS] Suzanna [RP]
<br />

<br />
This little thing would really help roleplayers to actually identify eachother!
<br />

<br />
Suzanna.<br />_________________<br />Arch Convoker Suzanna Dreamingheart
<br />
Mighty Mage!
<br />
<a href=http://p208.ezboard.com/bheroes795> Heroes of the Old Lands </a>
<br />
Lanys T'Vyl.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by SuzannaDreamingheart on Fri Sep 24, 2004 1:30 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
