				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some great ideas so far, I particularly like:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>naladini wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">continued revamp and tuning of the task system. Level 63 players should not be getting tasks that were designed for elemental geared level 65 players</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
/AGREE!!  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_wall.gif" alt="Brick wall" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Greygull wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">maybe an offical guild bank!</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Great idea!!  I hate seeing guild mules sit and rot, while no one keeps an accurate log of its items...  Someone could probably make use out of them!  Of course there would have to be some sort of restrictions put in place by leader/officers to prevent guildies from taking everything and leaving the guild =P
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Aamen wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Bazaar. 
<br />

<br />
Enable folks to sell without devoting a PC to /trader (proxy, consignment, whatever).</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
GREAT idea!  I would love to see a system similar to FFXI, where you could go to several bazaars around the world (bazaar, starting cities, EC, OT, FV, Velious cities, etc.) and sell your items in a closed "auction house" style system where the items being sold would be put up for bid by players, and could only be purchased in that particular bazaar.  You would make a minimum price that must be met before the item is sold, and players would make bids on the item until they came to a price that was greater than or equal to that minimum price.  If the player bids more than that, great!  The player who put the item up for bid would receive the money via the /claim command, or via some sort of mailbox-system in your bank.  Of course, some bazaars would be more popular than others, but you may find a good deal if you travel abroad and check all of the bazaars.
<br />

<br />
Hard to implement?  Not really, most of these places have banks already set up, how hard would it be to add a bazaar NPC or two in the same building?  Of course for the players who prefer the trader system, that would still be available in the bazaar zone.
<br />

<br />
The mailbox system could even be expanded to allow players to transfer items and money to other players, and vice-versa, even while the recipient is offline.  Now you may be thinking this will turn EQ into FFXI, but this is only a system of buying/selling items and sending/receiving items.  It has nothing to do with the game itself really, it just affects the economy and player convenience.  EQ will still be EQ.  Besides, have you taken a look at FFXI's player economy lately?  It's thriving.  Ours SUCKS.<br />_________________<br />--<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=559376" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arc</a>--
<br />
62nd level Arch Mage
<br />
Tunare Server
<br />
(Refuses to admit he's retired)</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Arcaenus on Fri Sep 24, 2004 9:02 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
