			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">before i say what i really think (that nothing is going to fix up the years of messy development for EQ1) i think they need to start listening to the (reasonable) user base and take advantage of what they say/suggest. there have been many postings here (and elsewhere) saying something is too hard/easy/difficult and offering a reasonable solution that wouldn't upset things. hell. that's free work that someone else has done testing something and coming up with a solution. i see sony asking time and time again what suggestions people have and then either ignoring them or doing something even worse.
<br />

<br />
anyway. the major problem with EQ is years of development. patches on top of patches. upgrades on top of downgrades on top of upgrades on top of downgrades. everything is out of balance, classes, hardcore vs. casual, pets, mobs, zones, equipment, quests.
<br />

<br />
EQ has been in development for years, developers have come and gone, designers have come and gone. new developers can't understand someone else's code and new designers have no idea what someone was thinking when they planned out a previous area/zone/quest/whatever.
<br />

<br />
what's going to fix EQ1? in the end, nothing short of re-creating the whole thing over again, which isn't going to happen. i've seen this thing happen on several muds that were up for years and years (anyone else here ever play batmud?).
<br />

<br />
sony's solution? EQ2. and hopefully they learned from their experience developing and running EQ1 so that they have a good strategy this time through that lasts few years before the same thing hits EQ2 (and it will, just give it time).
<br />

<br />
yes. we could all sit and say "fix pets", "fix this spell", "fix that item" and that's all nice little band-aids over a sinking ship. but if you step back and look at all of EQ, all of the complaints, bugs, problems, unbalanced issues, the only way to fix it would be to do it over. at least that's my humble opinion.
<br />

<br />
accept EQ1 for what it is. play it and enjoy it. hope there are some minor fixes/tweaks that won't hinder your enjoyment of the game. but if you're looking for something major to fix all your complaints, problems, going to Wow, EQ2, CoH, whatever is probably your best solution.<br />_________________<br />EQ1: Cannyar Coldmoon - 66 Magician - Xev - retired
