				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Things that would make a big difference in my personal playstyle (casual non-raider):
<br />

<br />
--Tune down epic 1.5 fights so casual guilds have a chance at completing them (already been mentioned).  I don't think anyone is looking for a gimpy quest that everyone and their alt will be able to get, but at least make it so there is HOPE to achieve this.  Right now I look at it and say, I might as well not even start, there's no way it's even possible, even when I do hit 70.  
<br />

<br />
--Attunable rocks.  I look at it like you're buying loot rights.  Go back and make some older items attunable.  Wand of the Ice Storm comes to mind.  
<br />

<br />
--I loved LDoN.  I can understand not adding elemental-style gear (it IS considered an older expansion now, i guess) but perhaps making the next expansion tied to LDoN (can share points) but with new dungeon layouts, a whole new tier of gear, maybe spell drops.  Oh yeah, and let people be able to switch players in and out of adventures, please.
<br />

<br />
--I also agree with the suggestion to either remove flags for more PoP zones, or make easier quests for smaller guilds to get in.
<br />

<br />
--Add search functions in bazaar for reccommended level, spell level, and augments.
<br />

<br />
--I want to send a tell to a friend who's offline.  Make it so that when he logs on, he gets the message that there is a tell in his mailbox to read.
<br />

<br />
Just some ideas off the top of my head.  I haven't actually thought these through too well, they are just some things that I, as a non-raider, would love to see.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
