			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Quick list for now:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Make Task rewards comparable to grouped XP/AA </span>
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Tasks should not involve dispelling mobs </span>
<br />

<br />
At 65, tasks were netting 4-6% XP per hour.  I expect this to be virtually none at 70, due to the mob levels.  I could farm low blues for 4% per hour with no risk of loss of buffs.  Most classes cannot self-buff with what they need for reasonably efficient AA/XP farming.  
<br />

<br />
Grouped, I could obtain 15-20% per hour.  At 65 or 70, AAs come every 30-60 minutes, with 30-40 being typical for us.  I accept SOE's desire to have grouping be more rewarding than soloing, but the promise was that thest Tasks were a viable alternative.  To me that means no worse than half the grouped AA rate, or about 60-90 minutes per AA.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Properly instance Time </span>
<br />

<br />
As this zone becomes more available to more guilds, the current (broken) pseudo-instancing will become more problematic.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Finish Tacvi </span>
<br />

<br />
Is this zone going to simply fade away as it is still apparently broken and the loots may well suck compared to what lies ahead in OoW?  Make sure the drops are comparable to OoW drops and finish tuning the content there please.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Backflagging </span>
<br />

<br />
Still a PITA.  Need some creative way to allow guild recruits to play with the guild.  "Piggy-backing" seemed reasonable in PoP.  Maybe other ideas?
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Reduce timer for leaving "lock-out" raid expeditions for corpse recovery </span>
<br />

<br />
Presently, leaving an raid expedition in GoD when you wipe and call it a day takes forever for corpses to pop, 30 minutes, I believe.  I can see a short timer for people that are inadvertently removed to be re-added, but why so long otherwise?  You can't get another instance and try again because of the lockout timer.  Make it intelligent, at the very least, e.g., if your corpse is in an instance with no people assigned to it, the corpse pops.  Let us lick our wounds and go to sleep after being humiliated by the mobs within.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Random major named spawn randomization </span>
<br />

<br />
If you don't play an East-Coast (or European or Asian) timeframe, many raid mobs are already taken by the time you start playing.  Make these mobs spawn based on a uniformly distributed, 24-hour window so that they are available to any timezone.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Universal Improved Invis </span>
<br />

<br />
Invis is an absolute essential for any play in GoD and OoW.  Assuming that the mage spell is the "solution" for this, I can see no reason not to make the clickie item; (a) non-Lore, (b) droppable, and (c) stackable.  People will just make mage invis `bots as they do for other classes (and CoH) anyways. If you want to keep it out of the hands of low-level players, simply put a Required Level of 50 or 55 on it.
<br />

<br />
EDIT -- Add <span style="font-weight: bold">targettable </span>to the summons please, these are going to be like rods and I sure as hell don't want to be running around handing them out.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Uniform CoH / Necro-vac </span>
<br />

<br />
Mentioned above -- simply limit the use of CoH and corpse summons in the same exact way, and only in those portions of zones deemed "exploitable." 
<br />

<br />
EDIT -- Add "GY code"  to portions zones so limited to allow for reasonable CR efforts, e.g., NToV, the far side of The Deep, the very top of Vxed, etc. Maybe make the corpses pop on the edge of the "restricted" area?
<br />

<br />
Note that this still does not prevent the die-drag-rez approach.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Improve video "spikiness" </span>
<br />

<br />
As of late, the video seems to "freeze up" for a few seconds.  I'll take smooth video over shiny water any day!
<br />

<br />

<br />
(Ignoring anything that I consider to be balance/power specific -- which includes a host of mage issues.)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Elementalist Itchyban of Veeshan</a>
<br />
"Nothing to see here. Move along. Move along." 
<br />
"These are not the droids you are looking for."</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by itchyban on Fri Sep 24, 2004 4:17 pm; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
